*This was a waste of time but she had to get Prowl out of this phase and 
into one where HE was the one in controle and not the beast, feeling his 
claws twist out of her back as he begins to fall towards the ground.
< Maybe if I broke a wing he wouldn't be able to take to the air again...> 
she thought quickly as she moved to snap her head around, jaws open, heading 
right for one of Prowl's wings.
< I'm tired of this.>
Prowl, by then, had already jerked his foot out of her mouth and she 
couldn't have ignored the pain in her neck if she had tried when Prowl bit 
down on it.
Iron Raptor growled as she heared Angey Prime's transmission.
< Not now! I'm busy!>
She hissed and moved her head to try and bite at Prowl's cheek but he had a 
pretty good hold on her now.*
